
  <sn><md>### Changed

Influential people are remembered for the changes they bring to society and for their contributions to human welfare. We feed our children and take care of our wives, parents, and families, but to me, these actions are not extraordinary acts of morality. They come naturally because God has placed love for them in our hearts. Motivated by these God-given feelings, we care for those closest to us.

However, the real test begins when we think beyond our immediate circle. It is about helping those who are not our relatives or close companions. It is about stepping outside our comfort zone and working for the well-being of others.

This is the path that determines how we can address the problems of our society. I believe that one day God will ask us what we have done for our people, our nation, and our community. We may not always succeed in creating the changes we desire, but God will surely see our intentions, our efforts, and the genuine concern we carried in our hearts for those changes.
</md></sn>
